129static void encodeSharedBuffer(Encoder& encoder, const SharedBuffer* buffer)
130{
131 bool isNull = !buffer;
132 encoder << isNull;
133 if (isNull)
134 return;
135
136 uint64_t bufferSize = buffer->size();
137 encoder << bufferSize;
138 if (!bufferSize)
139 return;
140
141#if USE(UNIX_DOMAIN_SOCKETS)
142 // Do not use shared memory for SharedBuffer encoding in Unix, because it's easy to reach the
143 // maximum number of file descriptors open per process when sending large data in small chunks
144 // over the IPC. ConnectionUnix.cpp already uses shared memory to send any IPC message that is
145 // too large. See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=208571.
146 for (const auto& element : *buffer)
147 encoder.encodeFixedLengthData(element.segment->data(), element.segment->size(), 1);
148#else
149 SharedMemory::Handle handle;
150 auto sharedMemoryBuffer = SharedMemory::copyBuffer(*buffer);
151 sharedMemoryBuffer->createHandle(handle, SharedMemory::Protection::ReadOnly);
152 encoder << SharedMemory::IPCHandle { WTFMove(handle), bufferSize };
153#endif
154}
155
156static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decodeSharedBuffer(Decoder& decoder, RefPtr<SharedBuffer>& buffer)
157{
158 std::optional<bool> isNull;
159 decoder >> isNull;
160 if (!isNull)
161 return false;
162
163 if (*isNull) {
164 buffer = nullptr;
165 return true;
166 }
167
168 uint64_t bufferSize = 0;
169 if (!decoder.decode(bufferSize))
170 return false;
171
172 if (!bufferSize) {
173 buffer = SharedBuffer::create();
174 return true;
175 }
176
177#if USE(UNIX_DOMAIN_SOCKETS)
178 if (!decoder.bufferIsLargeEnoughToContain<uint8_t>(bufferSize))
179 return false;
180
181 Vector<uint8_t> data;
182 data.grow(bufferSize);
183 if (!decoder.decodeFixedLengthData(data.data(), data.size(), 1))
184 return false;
185
186 buffer = SharedBuffer::create(WTFMove(data));
187#else
188 SharedMemory::IPCHandle ipcHandle;
189 if (!decoder.decode(ipcHandle))
190 return false;
191
192 auto sharedMemoryBuffer = SharedMemory::map(ipcHandle.handle, SharedMemory::Protection::ReadOnly);
193 if (!sharedMemoryBuffer)
194 return false;
195
196 if (sharedMemoryBuffer->size() < bufferSize)
197 return false;
198
199 buffer = SharedBuffer::create(static_cast<unsigned char*>(sharedMemoryBuffer->data()), bufferSize);
200#endif
201
202 return true;
203}
204
205static void encodeTypesAndData(Encoder& encoder, const Vector<String>& types, const Vector<RefPtr<SharedBuffer>>& data)
206{
207 ASSERT(types.size() == data.size());
208 encoder << types;
209 encoder << static_cast<uint64_t>(data.size());
210 for (auto& buffer : data)
211 encodeSharedBuffer(encoder, buffer.get());
212}
213
214static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decodeTypesAndData(Decoder& decoder, Vector<String>& types, Vector<RefPtr<SharedBuffer>>& data)
215{
216 if (!decoder.decode(types))
217 return false;
218
219 uint64_t dataSize;
220 if (!decoder.decode(dataSize))
221 return false;
222
223 ASSERT(dataSize == types.size());
224
225 for (uint64_t i = 0; i < dataSize; i++) {
226 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> buffer;
227 if (!decodeSharedBuffer(decoder, buffer))
228 return false;
229 data.append(WTFMove(buffer));
230 }
231
232 return true;
233}

245void ArgumentCoder<CacheQueryOptions>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const CacheQueryOptions& options)
246{
247 encoder << options.ignoreSearch;
248 encoder << options.ignoreMethod;
249 encoder << options.ignoreVary;
250 encoder << options.cacheName;
251}
252
253bool ArgumentCoder<CacheQueryOptions>::decode(Decoder& decoder, CacheQueryOptions& options)
254{
255 bool ignoreSearch;
256 if (!decoder.decode(ignoreSearch))
257 return false;
258 bool ignoreMethod;
259 if (!decoder.decode(ignoreMethod))
260 return false;
261 bool ignoreVary;
262 if (!decoder.decode(ignoreVary))
263 return false;
264 String cacheName;
265 if (!decoder.decode(cacheName))
266 return false;
267
268 options.ignoreSearch = ignoreSearch;
269 options.ignoreMethod = ignoreMethod;
270 options.ignoreVary = ignoreVary;
271 options.cacheName = WTFMove(cacheName);
272 return true;
273}

275void ArgumentCoder<CharacterRange>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const CharacterRange& range)
276{
277 encoder << static_cast<uint64_t>(range.location);
278 encoder << static_cast<uint64_t>(range.length);
279}
280
281std::optional<CharacterRange> ArgumentCoder<CharacterRange>::decode(Decoder& decoder)
282{
283 std::optional<uint64_t> location;
284 decoder >> location;
285 if (!location)
286 return std::nullopt;
287
288 std::optional<uint64_t> length;
289 decoder >> length;
290 if (!length)
291 return std::nullopt;
292
293 return { { *location, *length } };
294}

296void ArgumentCoder<DOMCacheEngine::CacheInfo>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const DOMCacheEngine::CacheInfo& info)
297{
298 encoder << info.identifier;
299 encoder << info.name;
300}
301
302auto ArgumentCoder<DOMCacheEngine::CacheInfo>::decode(Decoder& decoder) -> std::optional<DOMCacheEngine::CacheInfo>
303{
304 std::optional<uint64_t> identifier;
305 decoder >> identifier;
306 if (!identifier)
307 return std::nullopt;
308
309 std::optional<String> name;
310 decoder >> name;
311 if (!name)
312 return std::nullopt;
313
314 return {{ WTFMove(*identifier), WTFMove(*name) }};
315}

317void ArgumentCoder<DOMCacheEngine::Record>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const DOMCacheEngine::Record& record)
318{
319 encoder << record.identifier;
320
321 encoder << record.requestHeadersGuard;
322 encoder << record.request;
323 encoder << record.options;
324 encoder << record.referrer;
325
326 encoder << record.responseHeadersGuard;
327 encoder << record.response;
328 encoder << record.updateResponseCounter;
329 encoder << record.responseBodySize;
330
331 WTF::switchOn(record.responseBody, [&](const Ref<SharedBuffer>& buffer) {
332 encoder << true;
333 encodeSharedBuffer(encoder, buffer.ptr());
334 }, [&](const Ref<FormData>& formData) {
335 encoder << false;
336 encoder << true;
337 formData->encode(encoder);
338 }, [&](const std::nullptr_t&) {
339 encoder << false;
340 encoder << false;
341 });
342}
343
344std::optional<DOMCacheEngine::Record> ArgumentCoder<DOMCacheEngine::Record>::decode(Decoder& decoder)
345{
346 uint64_t identifier;
347 if (!decoder.decode(identifier))
348 return std::nullopt;
349
350 FetchHeaders::Guard requestHeadersGuard;
351 if (!decoder.decode(requestHeadersGuard))
352 return std::nullopt;
353
354 WebCore::ResourceRequest request;
355 if (!decoder.decode(request))
356 return std::nullopt;
357
358 std::optional<WebCore::FetchOptions> options;
359 decoder >> options;
360 if (!options)
361 return std::nullopt;
362
363 String referrer;
364 if (!decoder.decode(referrer))
365 return std::nullopt;
366
367 FetchHeaders::Guard responseHeadersGuard;
368 if (!decoder.decode(responseHeadersGuard))
369 return std::nullopt;
370
371 WebCore::ResourceResponse response;
372 if (!decoder.decode(response))
373 return std::nullopt;
374
375 uint64_t updateResponseCounter;
376 if (!decoder.decode(updateResponseCounter))
377 return std::nullopt;
378
379 uint64_t responseBodySize;
380 if (!decoder.decode(responseBodySize))
381 return std::nullopt;
382
383 WebCore::DOMCacheEngine::ResponseBody responseBody;
384 bool hasSharedBufferBody;
385 if (!decoder.decode(hasSharedBufferBody))
386 return std::nullopt;
387
388 if (hasSharedBufferBody) {
389 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> buffer;
390 if (!decodeSharedBuffer(decoder, buffer))
391 return std::nullopt;
392 if (buffer)
393 responseBody = buffer.releaseNonNull();
394 } else {
395 bool hasFormDataBody;
396 if (!decoder.decode(hasFormDataBody))
397 return std::nullopt;
398 if (hasFormDataBody) {
399 auto formData = FormData::decode(decoder);
400 if (!formData)
401 return std::nullopt;
402 responseBody = formData.releaseNonNull();
403 }
404 }
405
406 return {{ WTFMove(identifier), WTFMove(updateResponseCounter), WTFMove(requestHeadersGuard), WTFMove(request), WTFMove(options.value()), WTFMove(referrer), WTFMove(responseHeadersGuard), WTFMove(response), WTFMove(responseBody), responseBodySize }};
407}

409void ArgumentCoder<EventTrackingRegions>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const EventTrackingRegions& eventTrackingRegions)
410{
411 encoder << eventTrackingRegions.asynchronousDispatchRegion;
412 encoder << eventTrackingRegions.eventSpecificSynchronousDispatchRegions;
413}
414
415bool ArgumentCoder<EventTrackingRegions>::decode(Decoder& decoder, EventTrackingRegions& eventTrackingRegions)
416{
417 std::optional<Region> asynchronousDispatchRegion;
418 decoder >> asynchronousDispatchRegion;
419 if (!asynchronousDispatchRegion)
420 return false;
421 HashMap<String, Region> eventSpecificSynchronousDispatchRegions;
422 if (!decoder.decode(eventSpecificSynchronousDispatchRegions))
423 return false;
424 eventTrackingRegions.asynchronousDispatchRegion = WTFMove(*asynchronousDispatchRegion);
425 eventTrackingRegions.eventSpecificSynchronousDispatchRegions = WTFMove(eventSpecificSynchronousDispatchRegions);
426 return true;
427}

429void ArgumentCoder<TransformationMatrix>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const TransformationMatrix& transformationMatrix)
430{
431 encoder << transformationMatrix.m11();
432 encoder << transformationMatrix.m12();
433 encoder << transformationMatrix.m13();
434 encoder << transformationMatrix.m14();
435
436 encoder << transformationMatrix.m21();
437 encoder << transformationMatrix.m22();
438 encoder << transformationMatrix.m23();
439 encoder << transformationMatrix.m24();
440
441 encoder << transformationMatrix.m31();
442 encoder << transformationMatrix.m32();
443 encoder << transformationMatrix.m33();
444 encoder << transformationMatrix.m34();
445
446 encoder << transformationMatrix.m41();
447 encoder << transformationMatrix.m42();
448 encoder << transformationMatrix.m43();
449 encoder << transformationMatrix.m44();
450}
451
452bool ArgumentCoder<TransformationMatrix>::decode(Decoder& decoder, TransformationMatrix& transformationMatrix)
453{
454 double m11;
455 if (!decoder.decode(m11))
456 return false;
457 double m12;
458 if (!decoder.decode(m12))
459 return false;
460 double m13;
461 if (!decoder.decode(m13))
462 return false;
463 double m14;
464 if (!decoder.decode(m14))
465 return false;
466
467 double m21;
468 if (!decoder.decode(m21))
469 return false;
470 double m22;
471 if (!decoder.decode(m22))
472 return false;
473 double m23;
474 if (!decoder.decode(m23))
475 return false;
476 double m24;
477 if (!decoder.decode(m24))
478 return false;
479
480 double m31;
481 if (!decoder.decode(m31))
482 return false;
483 double m32;
484 if (!decoder.decode(m32))
485 return false;
486 double m33;
487 if (!decoder.decode(m33))
488 return false;
489 double m34;
490 if (!decoder.decode(m34))
491 return false;
492
493 double m41;
494 if (!decoder.decode(m41))
495 return false;
496 double m42;
497 if (!decoder.decode(m42))
498 return false;
499 double m43;
500 if (!decoder.decode(m43))
501 return false;
502 double m44;
503 if (!decoder.decode(m44))
504 return false;
505
506 transformationMatrix.setMatrix(m11, m12, m13, m14, m21, m22, m23, m24, m31, m32, m33, m34, m41, m42, m43, m44);
507 return true;
508}

521void ArgumentCoder<CubicBezierTimingFunction>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const CubicBezierTimingFunction& timingFunction)
522{
523 encoder << timingFunction.type();
524
525 encoder << timingFunction.x1();
526 encoder << timingFunction.y1();
527 encoder << timingFunction.x2();
528 encoder << timingFunction.y2();
529
530 encoder << timingFunction.timingFunctionPreset();
531}
532
533bool ArgumentCoder<CubicBezierTimingFunction>::decode(Decoder& decoder, CubicBezierTimingFunction& timingFunction)
534{
535 // Type is decoded by the caller.
536 double x1;
537 if (!decoder.decode(x1))
538 return false;
539
540 double y1;
541 if (!decoder.decode(y1))
542 return false;
543
544 double x2;
545 if (!decoder.decode(x2))
546 return false;
547
548 double y2;
549 if (!decoder.decode(y2))
550 return false;
551
552 CubicBezierTimingFunction::TimingFunctionPreset preset;
553 if (!decoder.decode(preset))
554 return false;
555
556 timingFunction.setValues(x1, y1, x2, y2);
557 timingFunction.setTimingFunctionPreset(preset);
558
559 return true;
560}

562void ArgumentCoder<StepsTimingFunction>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const StepsTimingFunction& timingFunction)
563{
564 encoder << timingFunction.type();
565
566 encoder << timingFunction.numberOfSteps();
567 encoder << timingFunction.stepPosition();
568}
569
570bool ArgumentCoder<StepsTimingFunction>::decode(Decoder& decoder, StepsTimingFunction& timingFunction)
571{
572 // Type is decoded by the caller.
573 int numSteps;
574 if (!decoder.decode(numSteps))
575 return false;
576
577 std::optional<StepsTimingFunction::StepPosition> stepPosition;
578 if (!decoder.decode(stepPosition))
579 return false;
580
581 timingFunction.setNumberOfSteps(numSteps);
582 timingFunction.setStepPosition(stepPosition);
583
584 return true;
585}

587void ArgumentCoder<SpringTimingFunction>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const SpringTimingFunction& timingFunction)
588{
589 encoder << timingFunction.type();
590
591 encoder << timingFunction.mass();
592 encoder << timingFunction.stiffness();
593 encoder << timingFunction.damping();
594 encoder << timingFunction.initialVelocity();
595}
596
597bool ArgumentCoder<SpringTimingFunction>::decode(Decoder& decoder, SpringTimingFunction& timingFunction)
598{
599 // Type is decoded by the caller.
600 double mass;
601 if (!decoder.decode(mass))
602 return false;
603
604 double stiffness;
605 if (!decoder.decode(stiffness))
606 return false;
607
608 double damping;
609 if (!decoder.decode(damping))
610 return false;
611
612 double initialVelocity;
613 if (!decoder.decode(initialVelocity))
614 return false;
615
616 timingFunction.setValues(mass, stiffness, damping, initialVelocity);
617
618 return true;
619}

964void ArgumentCoder<ProtectionSpace>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const ProtectionSpace& space)
965{
966 if (space.encodingRequiresPlatformData()) {
967 encoder << true;
968 encodePlatformData(encoder, space);
969 return;

971
972 encoder << false;

974 encoder << space.authenticationScheme();
975 encoder << space.serverType();

979{

986
987 String host;
988 if (!decoder.decode(host))
989 return false;
990
991 int port;
992 if (!decoder.decode(port))
993 return false;
994
995 String realm;
996 if (!decoder.decode(realm))
997 return false;
998
999 ProtectionSpaceAuthenticationScheme authenticationScheme;
1000 if (!decoder.decode(authenticationScheme))
1001 return false;
1002
1003 ProtectionSpaceServerType serverType;
1004 if (!decoder.decode(serverType))
1005 return false;
1006
1007 space = ProtectionSpace(host, port, serverType, realm, authenticationScheme);
1008 return true;

1049static void encodeImage(Encoder& encoder, Image& image)
1050{
1051 RefPtr<ShareableBitmap> bitmap = ShareableBitmap::createShareable(IntSize(image.size()), { });
1052 auto graphicsContext = bitmap->createGraphicsContext();
1053 encoder << !!graphicsContext;
1054 if (!graphicsContext)
1055 return;
1056
1057 graphicsContext->drawImage(image, IntPoint());
1058
1059 ShareableBitmap::Handle handle;
1060 bitmap->createHandle(handle);
1061
1062 encoder << handle;
1063}
1064
1065static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decodeImage(Decoder& decoder, RefPtr<Image>& image)
1066{
1067 std::optional<bool> didCreateGraphicsContext;
1068 decoder >> didCreateGraphicsContext;
1069 if (!didCreateGraphicsContext || !*didCreateGraphicsContext)
1070 return false;
1071
1072 ShareableBitmap::Handle handle;
1073 if (!decoder.decode(handle))
1074 return false;
1075
1076 RefPtr<ShareableBitmap> bitmap = ShareableBitmap::create(handle);
1077 if (!bitmap)
1078 return false;
1079 image = bitmap->createImage();
1080 if (!image)
1081 return false;
1082 return true;
1083}
1084
1085static void encodeOptionalImage(Encoder& encoder, Image* image)
1086{
1087 bool hasImage = !!image;
1088 encoder << hasImage;
1089
1090 if (hasImage)
1091 encodeImage(encoder, *image);
1092}
1093
1094static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decodeOptionalImage(Decoder& decoder, RefPtr<Image>& image)
1095{
1096 image = nullptr;
1097
1098 bool hasImage;
1099 if (!decoder.decode(hasImage))
1100 return false;
1101
1102 if (!hasImage)
1103 return true;
1104
1105 return decodeImage(decoder, image);
1106}

1108void ArgumentCoder<Ref<Font>>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const Ref<WebCore::Font>& font)
1109{
1110 encoder << font->origin();
1111 encoder << (font->isInterstitial() ? Font::Interstitial::Yes : Font::Interstitial::No);
1112 encoder << font->visibility();
1113 encoder << (font->isTextOrientationFallback() ? Font::OrientationFallback::Yes : Font::OrientationFallback::No);
1114 encoder << font->renderingResourceIdentifier();
1115 // Intentionally don't encode m_isBrokenIdeographFallback because it doesn't affect drawGlyphs().
1116
1117 encodePlatformData(encoder, font);
1118}
1119
1120std::optional<Ref<Font>> ArgumentCoder<Ref<Font>>::decode(Decoder& decoder)
1121{
1122 std::optional<Font::Origin> origin;
1123 decoder >> origin;
1124 if (!origin)
1125 return std::nullopt;
1126
1127 std::optional<Font::Interstitial> isInterstitial;
1128 decoder >> isInterstitial;
1129 if (!isInterstitial)
1130 return std::nullopt;
1131
1132 std::optional<Font::Visibility> visibility;
1133 decoder >> visibility;
1134 if (!visibility)
1135 return std::nullopt;
1136
1137 std::optional<Font::OrientationFallback> isTextOrientationFallback;
1138 decoder >> isTextOrientationFallback;
1139 if (!isTextOrientationFallback)
1140 return std::nullopt;
1141
1142 std::optional<RenderingResourceIdentifier> renderingRersouceIdentifier;
1143 decoder >> renderingRersouceIdentifier;
1144 if (!renderingRersouceIdentifier)
1145 return std::nullopt;
1146
1147 auto platformData = decodePlatformData(decoder);
1148 if (!platformData)
1149 return std::nullopt;
1150
1151 return Font::create(platformData.value(), origin.value(), isInterstitial.value(), visibility.value(), isTextOrientationFallback.value(), renderingRersouceIdentifier);
1152}
1153
1154void ArgumentCoder<Cursor>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const Cursor& cursor)
1155{
1156 encoder << cursor.type();
1157
1158 if (cursor.type() != Cursor::Custom)
1159 return;
1160
1161 if (cursor.image()->isNull()) {
1162 encoder << false; // There is no valid image being encoded.
1163 return;
1164 }
1165
1166 encoder << true;
1167 encodeImage(encoder, *cursor.image());
1168 encoder << cursor.hotSpot();
1169#if ENABLE(MOUSE_CURSOR_SCALE)
1170 encoder << cursor.imageScaleFactor();
1171#endif
1172}
1173
1174bool ArgumentCoder<Cursor>::decode(Decoder& decoder, Cursor& cursor)
1175{
1176 Cursor::Type type;
1177 if (!decoder.decode(type))
1178 return false;
1179
1180 if (type > Cursor::Custom)
1181 return false;
1182
1183 if (type != Cursor::Custom) {
1184 const Cursor& cursorReference = Cursor::fromType(type);
1185 // Calling platformCursor here will eagerly create the platform cursor for the cursor singletons inside WebCore.
1186 // This will avoid having to re-create the platform cursors over and over.
1187 (void)cursorReference.platformCursor();
1188
1189 cursor = cursorReference;
1190 return true;
1191 }
1192
1193 bool isValidImagePresent;
1194 if (!decoder.decode(isValidImagePresent))
1195 return false;
1196
1197 if (!isValidImagePresent) {
1198 cursor = Cursor(&Image::nullImage(), IntPoint());
1199 return true;
1200 }
1201
1202 RefPtr<Image> image;
1203 if (!decodeImage(decoder, image))
1204 return false;
1205
1206 IntPoint hotSpot;
1207 if (!decoder.decode(hotSpot))
1208 return false;
1209
1210 if (!image->rect().contains(hotSpot))
1211 return false;
1212
1213#if ENABLE(MOUSE_CURSOR_SCALE)
1214 float scale;
1215 if (!decoder.decode(scale))
1216 return false;
1217
1218 cursor = Cursor(image.get(), hotSpot, scale);
1219#else
1220 cursor = Cursor(image.get(), hotSpot);
1221#endif
1222 return true;
1223}

1225void ArgumentCoder<ResourceRequest>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const ResourceRequest& resourceRequest)
1226{
1227 encoder << resourceRequest.cachePartition();
1228 encoder << resourceRequest.hiddenFromInspector();
1229
1230#if USE(SYSTEM_PREVIEW)
1231 if (resourceRequest.isSystemPreview()) {
1232 encoder << true;
1233 encoder << resourceRequest.systemPreviewInfo();
1234 } else
1235 encoder << false;
1236#endif
1237
1238 if (resourceRequest.encodingRequiresPlatformData()) {
1239 encoder << true;
1240 encodePlatformData(encoder, resourceRequest);
1241 return;
1242 }
1243 encoder << false;
1244 resourceRequest.encodeWithoutPlatformData(encoder);
1245}
1246
1247bool ArgumentCoder<ResourceRequest>::decode(Decoder& decoder, ResourceRequest& resourceRequest)
1248{
1249 String cachePartition;
1250 if (!decoder.decode(cachePartition))
1251 return false;
1252 resourceRequest.setCachePartition(cachePartition);
1253
1254 bool isHiddenFromInspector;
1255 if (!decoder.decode(isHiddenFromInspector))
1256 return false;
1257 resourceRequest.setHiddenFromInspector(isHiddenFromInspector);
1258
1259#if USE(SYSTEM_PREVIEW)
1260 bool isSystemPreview;
1261 if (!decoder.decode(isSystemPreview))
1262 return false;
1263
1264 if (isSystemPreview) {
1265 SystemPreviewInfo systemPreviewInfo;
1266 if (!decoder.decode(systemPreviewInfo))
1267 return false;
1268 resourceRequest.setSystemPreviewInfo(systemPreviewInfo);
1269 }
1270#endif
1271
1272 bool hasPlatformData;
1273 if (!decoder.decode(hasPlatformData))
1274 return false;
1275 if (hasPlatformData)
1276 return decodePlatformData(decoder, resourceRequest);
1277
1278 return resourceRequest.decodeWithoutPlatformData(decoder);
1279}

1281void ArgumentCoder<ResourceError>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const ResourceError& resourceError)
1282{
1283 encoder << resourceError.type();
1284 if (resourceError.type() == ResourceError::Type::Null)
1285 return;
1286 encodePlatformData(encoder, resourceError);
1287}
1288
1289bool ArgumentCoder<ResourceError>::decode(Decoder& decoder, ResourceError& resourceError)
1290{
1291 ResourceError::Type type;
1292 if (!decoder.decode(type))
1293 return false;
1294
1295 if (type == ResourceError::Type::Null) {
1296 resourceError = { };
1297 return true;
1298 }
1299
1300 if (!decodePlatformData(decoder, resourceError))
1301 return false;
1302
1303 resourceError.setType(type);
1304 return true;
1305}

1562template<> struct ArgumentCoder<PasteboardCustomData::Entry> {
1563 static void encode(Encoder&, const PasteboardCustomData::Entry&);
1564 static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decode(Decoder&, PasteboardCustomData::Entry&);
1565};
1566
1567void ArgumentCoder<PasteboardCustomData::Entry>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const PasteboardCustomData::Entry& data)
1568{
1569 encoder << data.type << data.customData;
1570
1571 auto& platformData = data.platformData;
1572 bool hasString = WTF::holds_alternative<String>(platformData);
1573 encoder << hasString;
1574 if (hasString)
1575 encoder << WTF::get<String>(platformData);
1576
1577 bool hasBuffer = WTF::holds_alternative<Ref<SharedBuffer>>(platformData);
1578 encoder << hasBuffer;
1579 if (hasBuffer)

1583bool ArgumentCoder<PasteboardCustomData::Entry>::decode(Decoder& decoder, PasteboardCustomData::Entry& data)
1584{

1586 return false;
1587
1588 if (!decoder.decode(data.customData))
1589 return false;
1590
1591 bool hasString;
1592 if (!decoder.decode(hasString))
1593 return false;
1594
1595 if (hasString) {
1596 String value;
1597 if (!decoder.decode(value))
1598 return false;
1599 data.platformData = { WTFMove(value) };
1600 }
1601
1602 bool hasBuffer;
1603 if (!decoder.decode(hasBuffer))
1604 return false;
1605
1606 if (hasString && hasBuffer)
1607 return false;
1608
1609 if (hasBuffer) {
1610 RefPtr<SharedBuffer> value;
1611 if (!decodeSharedBuffer(decoder, value) || !value)
1612 return false;
1613 data.platformData = { value.releaseNonNull() };
1614 }
1615
1616 return true;
1617}

2229void ArgumentCoder<FilterOperation>::encode(Encoder& encoder, const FilterOperation& filter)
2230{
2231 encoder << filter.type();

2234 case FilterOperation::NONE:
2235 case FilterOperation::REFERENCE:
2236 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();

2238 case FilterOperation::GRAYSCALE:
2239 case FilterOperation::SEPIA:
2240 case FilterOperation::SATURATE:
2241 case FilterOperation::HUE_ROTATE:

2243 return;
2244 case FilterOperation::INVERT:

2249 return;
2250 case FilterOperation::APPLE_INVERT_LIGHTNESS:
2251 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED(); // APPLE_INVERT_LIGHTNESS is only used in -apple-color-filter.
2252 return;
2253 case FilterOperation::BLUR:
2254 encoder << downcast<BlurFilterOperation>(filter).stdDeviation();
2255 return;
2256 case FilterOperation::DROP_SHADOW: {

2259 encoder << dropShadowFilter.stdDeviation();

2272
2273bool decodeFilterOperation(Decoder& decoder, RefPtr<FilterOperation>& filter)
2274{
2275 FilterOperation::OperationType type;
2276 if (!decoder.decode(type))
2277 return false;
2278
2279 switch (type) {
2280 case FilterOperation::NONE:
2281 case FilterOperation::REFERENCE:
2282 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2283 return false;
2284 case FilterOperation::GRAYSCALE:
2285 case FilterOperation::SEPIA:
2286 case FilterOperation::SATURATE:
2287 case FilterOperation::HUE_ROTATE: {
2288 double amount;
2289 if (!decoder.decode(amount))
2290 return false;
2291 filter = BasicColorMatrixFilterOperation::create(amount, type);
2292 return true;
2293 }
2294 case FilterOperation::INVERT:
2295 case FilterOperation::OPACITY:
2296 case FilterOperation::BRIGHTNESS:
2297 case FilterOperation::CONTRAST: {
2298 double amount;
2299 if (!decoder.decode(amount))
2300 return false;
2301 filter = BasicComponentTransferFilterOperation::create(amount, type);
2302 return true;
2303 }
2304 case FilterOperation::APPLE_INVERT_LIGHTNESS:
2305 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED(); // APPLE_INVERT_LIGHTNESS is only used in -apple-color-filter.
2306 return false;
2307 case FilterOperation::BLUR: {
2308 Length stdDeviation;
2309 if (!decoder.decode(stdDeviation))
2310 return false;
2311 filter = BlurFilterOperation::create(stdDeviation);
2312 return true;
2313 }
2314 case FilterOperation::DROP_SHADOW: {
2315 IntPoint location;
2316 int stdDeviation;
2317 Color color;
2318 if (!decoder.decode(location))
2319 return false;
2320 if (!decoder.decode(stdDeviation))
2321 return false;
2322 if (!decoder.decode(color))
2323 return false;
2324 filter = DropShadowFilterOperation::create(location, stdDeviation, color);
2325 return true;
2326 }
2327 case FilterOperation::DEFAULT: {
2328 FilterOperation::OperationType representedType;
2329 if (!decoder.decode(representedType))
2330 return false;
2331 filter = DefaultFilterOperation::create(representedType);
2332 return true;
2333 }
2334 case FilterOperation::PASSTHROUGH:
2335 filter = PassthroughFilterOperation::create();
2336 return true;
2337 }
2338
2339 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2340 return false;
2341}

3057#if ENABLE(SHAREABLE_RESOURCE) && PLATFORM(COCOA)
3058static ShareableResource::Handle tryConvertToShareableResourceHandle(const ScriptBuffer& script)
3059{
3060 if (!script.containsSingleFileMappedSegment())
3061 return ShareableResource::Handle { };
3062
3063 auto& segment = script.buffer()->begin()->segment;
3064 auto sharedMemory = SharedMemory::wrapMap(const_cast<uint8_t*>(segment->data()), segment->size(), SharedMemory::Protection::ReadOnly);
3065 if (!sharedMemory)
3066 return ShareableResource::Handle { };
3067
3068 auto shareableResource = ShareableResource::create(sharedMemory.releaseNonNull(), 0, segment->size());
3069 if (!shareableResource)
3070 return ShareableResource::Handle { };
3071
3072 ShareableResource::Handle shareableResourceHandle;
3073 shareableResource->createHandle(shareableResourceHandle);
3074 return shareableResourceHandle;
3075}
3076
3077static std::optional<WebCore::ScriptBuffer> decodeScriptBufferAsShareableResourceHandle(Decoder& decoder)
3078{
3079 ShareableResource::Handle handle;
3080 if (!decoder.decode(handle) || handle.isNull())
3081 return std::nullopt;
3082 auto buffer = handle.tryWrapInSharedBuffer();
